news.title: Edelweiss fund to provide Rs 350 crore debt to Adarsh Developers entity
news.para: Shreshta Infra, an Adarsh Developers' special purpose vehicle, plans to on-lend Rs 200 crore to its affiliates and allocate the remaining Rs 150 crore for project financing and general corporate purposes, providing a financial blueprint for future real estate ventures.

news.title: Hyderabad: Three years on, pattadar passbooks not yet issued for 18 lakh acres
news.para: With 16 lakh acres of land in Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority districts such as Rangareddy, Medchal Malkajgiri and Sangareddy lying idle thanks to the Dharani prohibited list, urban planners and experts expressed concern over one of the major economic resources going waste.

news.title: Give 64 acres in Mulund for rental homes for Dharavi squatters, Maharashtra tells BMC
news.para: The letter says DRPPL has to build rental housing for residents found ineligible for free housing. “Rental housing is to be constructed for around 3-4 lakh ineligible people,” it says.

news.title: Bengaluru: Site allotment process begins in new BDA layout after eight years
news.para: Announcing this on Wednesday, deputy chief minister DK Shivakumar said following a review meeting with BDA officials that after giving priority to landowners who had lost their land for the project, the government agency will be left with about 10,000 sites for sale.

news.title: Land records in 236 taluks of state being digitised: Karnataka revenue minister
news.para: It’s aimed at curbing fraudulent property transactions, he stated, adding that it avoids forgery through the manipulation of land records.

news.title: DDA invites buyers in phase-II e-auction
news.para: While the registration and submission of the earnest money deposit (EMD) will start at 11am, the last date of the online registration and the submission of online EMD is Jan 29, said an official.

news.title: Cement producers to see 80-100% surge in profits for December quarter
news.para: After clocking double-digit volume expansion in the first half of the year, growth of these companies in Oct-Dec is seen moderating to around 5-6% for most players due to elections in some states, a construction ban in the NCR region and shortage of labor.

news.title: Now, pay stamp duty on carpet area for homes in West Bengal
news.para: According to RERA, real estate players had to sell flats as per carpet area. Earlier, in the state flats and houses had to be registered as per super built area.

news.title: Table Space, Runwal ink 10-year, Rs 333-crore Mumbai office lease deal
news.para: The cumulative rental payout for the transaction is over Rs 333 crore through the total term. The agreement includes a provision that grants Table Space an option to lease an additional 1.97 lakh sq ft of office space, thereby expanding the total deal size to nearly 3.30 lakh sq ft.

news.title: NCLAT set asides show cause notice against lenders over liquidation of SARE Realty Projects without bids
news.para: ​The appellate tribunal said there is an "error in the approach" of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) for taking a decision regarding the liquidation of a corporate debtor (CD) and the lenders have to complete all the steps regarding resolution.

news.title: Keystone Realtors to acquire 50% equity holding in Ajmera Luxe Realty
news.para: Cost of acquisition is Rs. 50,000. Net worth of Ajmera Luxe Realty as on March 31, 2023 was Rs. 92,000.

news.title: China's property market slide worsens despite government support
news.para: New home prices in December logged their steepest drop since February 2015, while property sales measured by floor area fell 23% in December from a year earlier, data from the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) showed on Wednesday.

news.title: Italy new home loan rates ease in December, corporate debt costs rise
news.para: ABI Deputy Director General Gianfranco Torriero told a media call it was the first proper drop in 24 months, while other apparent falls over this period had been caused by changes in the relative weight of floating and fixed-rate mortgages.

news.title: Asian Paints' profit jumps 34% to Rs 1,475 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Asian Paints' revenue from operations went up 5.4 per cent to Rs 9,103.09 crore during the quarter. In the year-ago period, it stood at Rs 8,636.74 crore.

news.title: Building supplier Geberit expects construction market decline in 2024
news.para: "Due to the challenging macroeconomic conditions and the ongoing geopolitical risks, the building construction industry is expected to decline overall in the current year," Geberit said.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body aims to finish smart city project by June 2024
news.para: M Vinay Kumar spoke to a group of journalists from Punjab who came to study the developmental programmes being undertaken by Union government under the “Vikasit Bharat Sankalp Yatra” (VBY).

news.title: Rajasthan: Realty boost with higher stamp, registration duty mopup this year
news.para: The collections rose to Rs 7010.22 crore in April-January (first 10 days of the current month) against Rs 6220.54 crore during the same period last financial year.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body to auction 110 properties for defaulting on tax
news.para: Civic officials have sent details of these 110 properties to the town planning department for valuation as per updated rates, and the auction will begin after the evaluation is done. This is the first auction of seized properties by PCMC.

news.title: Initiate action against illegal sand quarrying: Madras HC
news.para: The court was hearing a public interest litigation filed by S Sevugan and G Bharathiraja seeking a direction to prevent illegal sand quarrying in Kottagudi village.
